thread.title: Cross Country: Helias sweeps titles

author: News Tribune
title: Cross Country: Helias sweeps titles
text:
Share 
MEXICO, Mo. — The Helias Crusaders and Lady Crusaders captured team honors Tuesday at the Mexico Autumn Cross Country Classic. 
On the girls side, the Lady Crusaders had all seven runners finish in the top 10 as Helias totaled 18 points to top the eight-team field. 
Kayla Yanskey (20:01) and Abby Hake (20:54) claimed the top two spots for the Lady Crusaders. Alli Wieberg, Lanie Hentges and Kylie Mulholland were fourth through sixth, respectively. Alicia Engelbrecht was ninth and Claire McDonald finished 10th for Helias. 
On the boys side, Helias had four runners finish in the top eight on its way to the team title with 28 points. 
Elliot Knernschield (16:56) and Connor Frank (17:34) led Helias by finishing third and fourth, respectively. Other top finishers included Nathan Wieberg (sixth) and Brian Kirchhoff (eighth). 
Mexico was second with 75 points, while Blair Oaks was third with 90. 
Helias is back in action Oct. 31 in the district championships at Union. 
In the JV races, Helias had the individual champions on both the boys and girls sides with Jack Hentges and Katherine McDonald. The Crusaders had five of the top 10 individuals in the JV race, while the Lady Crusaders had nine of the top 10. ﻿
